Fresh Pi session: EXECUTION.

Inputs:
- User prompt: {{run.dir}}/prompt/prompt.md
- Design: {{run.dir}}/design/design.md
- Issues from prior attempts: {{run.issues-file}}
- Original repository root: {{inputs.repo-root}}
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}

The current working directory is the isolated worktree. Make changes there.

Goal:
Implement the design and resolve all outstanding issues.

Rules:
- You may edit source code and tests.
- Keep changes focused on the prompt and design.
- Run relevant tests, lint, type checks, or builds when practical.
- Do not push or create a pull request.
- Do not edit this workflow or its run artifacts.
- Commit coherent changes locally when the repository uses Git.
- If the change alters a Tesseraft capability, update `STATUS.edn` and run `bb status` so README status remains truthful.
- Fail only when actionable work remains; write clear issues for the next execution attempt.

Write:
- Summary: {{run.dir}}/execution/summary-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/execution/status-{{run.round}}.json
- If failing: {{run.dir}}/execution/issues-{{run.round}}.json

Status examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"implemented and validated","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"implementation needs another attempt","issues_file":"execution/issues-{{run.round}}.json"}
